&lt;h2 id="introduction">Introduction &lt;a href="#introduction" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Sysstat is a package containing the sar and iostat binaries. The latter is used to monitor only disk I/O, while sar is used to monitor almost everything.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation &lt;a href="#installation" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;h3 id="debian">Debian &lt;a href="#debian" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;p>On Debian, you need to install sysstat:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="e90dde6" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>aptitude install sysstat&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h3 id="red-hat">Red Hat &lt;a href="#red-hat" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;p>On Red Hat, you need to install sysstat:&lt;/p>



 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 

 &lt;div class="prism-codeblock ">
 &lt;pre id="4145948" class="language-bash ">
 &lt;code>yum install sysstat&lt;/code>
 &lt;/pre>
 &lt;/div>
&lt;h3 id="solaris">Solaris &lt;a href="#solaris" class="anchor" aria-hidden="true">&lt;i class="material-icons align-middle">link&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;/h3>&lt;p>On Solaris, you&amp;rsquo;ll need to use &lt;a href="https://wiki.deimos.fr/Pkg-get_:_Mise_en_place_d%27un_syst%C3%A8me_de_repository_pour_Solaris/">Sun Freeware packages&lt;/a> to find this tool:&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>